org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.streams.spi

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.streams.spi.Graph

  • public class Graph
extends Object
    A graph.

    Reactive Streams engines are required to convert the stages of this graph into a stream with interfaces according to the shape. The shape is governed by whether the graph has an inlet, an outlet, neither or both.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Graph

        public Graph(Collection<Stage> stages)
        Create a graph from the given stages.

        The stages of this graph will be validated to ensure that connect properly, that is, every stage but the first stage must have an inlet to receive a stream from the previous stage, and every stage but the last stage must have an outlet to produce a stream from the next stage.

        If the first stage has an inlet, then this graph has an inlet, and can therefore be represented as a Subscriber. If the last stage has an outlet, then this graph has an outlet, and therefore can be represented as a Publisher.

        Parameters:
        stages - The stages.
